- Symptom: a feasibility answer becomes muddled between what is technically possible and what is allowed to ship. Cause: mixing runtime architecture and auth/policy constraints together. Fix: separate technical feasibility from public distribution/auth feasibility early in the answer [Task 1]
- Symptom: the app design overpromises Claude account parity. Cause: assuming public `claude.ai` login and subscription rate-limit mirroring are freely available. Fix: preserve Anthropic’s policy boundary and avoid promising those surfaces without prior approval [Task 1]
- Symptom: a Claude integration design drifts toward terminal scraping. Cause: treating the CLI as a TUI to parse instead of using the official headless interface. Fix: build around `claude -p` JSON/stream-json output and verified auth/runtime commands [Task 2]
- Symptom: usage/mode UI becomes brittle. Cause: treating experimental or optional runtime fields as guaranteed. Fix: feature-detect status fields and degrade gracefully when the runtime does not expose them [Task 1][Task 3]
- Symptom: a checklist is too abstract to build from. Cause: it lists ideas instead of architecture slices and acceptance gates. Fix: organize it around auth, runtime, data model, UI, approvals, worktrees, performance, and deployment constraints with measurable checkpoints [Task 3]

